IMPORTANT — SCOPE OF THIS LICENCE

This licence applies to the written documentation only.

The 512 constraint set — the seven invariants defining
execution-time legitimacy — is not owned by any person or
entity. It cannot be licensed because it is not ownable.
It was discovered, not invented. Physics and scale force it
into existence regardless of whether any specific
documentation exists.

No person may claim copyright, patent, or proprietary rights
over the 512 constraint set itself.

Anyone may build systems that satisfy 512's properties.
No permission is required. No licence is needed. No
attribution is required for the constraint set — only for
the written documentation in this repository if reproduced.

